article.headline: Robert Morris 69, Quinnipiac 64
article.story: MOON TOWNSHIP, Pa. -- Jeremy Chappell hit all three of his free throws in the final minutes and finished with 17 points, and Robert Morris rallied to beat Quinnipiac 69-64 Saturday night. Rob Robinson had 22 points and 14 rebounds for Robert Morris (19-8, 13-1 Northeast Conference), which outscored Quinnipiac 6-1 over the final 2:30 for the win. James Feldeine scored 25 points, and Jeremy Baker and Bryan Geffen each scored 11 for Quinnipiac (11-14, 7-7), which converted its last field goal with 3:28 remaining and squandered a late three-point lead. Robert Morris outscored Quinnipiac 29-20 in the paint and 29-15 off turnovers.
